As of #1544 you get to name your entrypoint. This applies to both single-script actions:

    function myMain(args) = { ... }

...and Node module actions:

    function something(args) = { ... }
    modules.exports.myHandler = something;

Both are achieved through the `--main` flag with the CLI. The pattern is the same for Swift and Python, and for Java `--main` specifies the fully-qualified class name.

We do not support `module.exports = function (args) { ... }` (i.e. top-level export is treated as main).

I move to mark as resolved?
